
<h2 class="display-6">
    What is CSS?
</h2>

<p>
    <strong>Cascading style sheets</strong>, or <strong>CSS</strong>, is a way to style 
    html websites with little effort. Css can be referenced 
    from an <strong>external</strong> file, called a stylesheet, that is accessed by the 
    link tag. The other ways are inline, which uses the style attribute, 
    and internal, which uses the style tag. 
</p>
<p>
    The most common way to use CSS is through external <b>stylesheets</b>. It 
    takes selectors and styles them according to the declaration. Inside the declaration
        there is the property and then the value. 
</p>
<p>
    <h3>
        Rulesets (Stylesheet Syntax):
    </h3> 
    <ul>
        <li>
            Selectors
            <pre data-line="1" class="lang-css"><code>p {
    color: blue;
}</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>
            Declaration Blocks
            <pre data-line="1-3" class="lang-css"><code><span>p</span> {
    color: blue;
}</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>
            Declarations
            <pre data-line="2" class="lang-css"><code><span>p</span> {
     color: blue; 
}</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>
            Properties
        </li>
        <pre data-line="2" class="lang-css"><code><span>p</span> {
     /* property --> */  color : blue;
}</code></pre>
        <li>
            Values
            <pre  data-line="2"  class="lang-css"><code><span>p</span> {
    color :  blue /* <-- Value  */ ;
}</code></pre>
        </li>
    </ul>
</p>
